The paper proposes a novel framework for efficient multi-task reinforcement learning, which involves training agents to employ hierarchical policies and acquire new skills continually. This work involves machine learning and artificial intelligence techniques, which are typically covered in the cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper uses a stochastic temporal grammar to help the agent learn complex temporal dependencies, which falls under the cs.CL (Computation and Language) sub-category. The paper also validates its approach on Minecraft games, which involves computer vision and robotics techniques, covered in the cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.RO (Robotics) sub-categories.
